{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-template-js","path":"/linux/get-time-from-remote-db","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Getting time from a remote database can be a simple way to maintain consistency across distributed systems, which is important for ensuring accurate logging and auditing of system activity.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token assign-left variable\">REMOTE_IP</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token number\">192.168</span>.1.2\n<span class=\"token assign-left variable\">POSTGRES_USER</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span>user\n<span class=\"token assign-left variable\">POSTGRES_DB</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span>db\n<span class=\"token assign-left variable\">CONNECTION_CONFIG</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"-h <span class=\"token variable\">$REMOTE_IP</span> -U <span class=\"token variable\">$POSTGRES_USER</span> -d <span class=\"token variable\">$POSTGRES_DB</span>\"</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">until</span> pg_isready <span class=\"token variable\">$CONNECTION_CONFIG</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">do</span> <span class=\"token function\">sleep</span> <span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">done</span>\npsql <span class=\"token variable\">$CONNECTION_CONFIG</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-c</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"select timeofday();\"</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">|</span> <span class=\"token function\">sed</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-n</span> 3p <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">|</span> <span class=\"token function\">xargs</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-i</span> <span class=\"token function\">date</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-s</span> <span class=\"token string\">'{}'</span></code></pre></div>","excerpt":"Getting time from a remote database can be a simple way to maintain consistency across distributed systems, which is important for ensuring…","tableOfContents":"","fields":{"socialcard":"gatsby-plugin-social-card/5970632f-4032-533b-a4ee-14932f0d2f8d.jpg"},"frontmatter":{"date":"November 02, 2021","published":"November 02, 2021","lastModified":"November 02, 2021","title":"Get time from remote DB","subtitle":null,"section":null,"draft":null,"developing":null,"buttonText":null,"buttonLink":null,"secondButtonText":null,"secondButtonLink":null,"featuredImage":null}}},"pageContext":{"showLikes":true,"absolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/linux/get-time-from-remote-db.md","url":"/linux/get-time-from-remote-db","next":{"excerpt":"Fingerprint / thumbprint Serial number Expiration date Convert to Java keystore Verify Code exaples: Java TCP secure server socket","fileAbsolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/linux/ssl-certificates.md","frontmatter":{"title":"SSL Certificates","date":"2022-01-30T00:00:00.000Z","topic":null,"article":null},"id":"16b2809e-edb3-5a4a-9219-08fa5e056dcf"},"previous":{"excerpt":"If you are experiencing network connectivity issues, knowing the time when a DHCP lease was created can help you to identify  whether a…","fileAbsolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/linux/get-time-when-lease-was-created.md","frontmatter":{"title":"Network Manager - DHCP lease","date":"2021-11-02T00:00:00.000Z","topic":null,"article":null},"id":"9c4179a1-97a4-5890-a9ed-09e75b52a5f5"},"recentArticles":[{"excerpt":"The time is now. So you are following the official path","fileAbsolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/mark